|CKBStreet Samurai: First Deployment|000

|CKB1. Verify the installation|000
|CK0Joining installs a prototype-grade Cortex OS automatically. Run dashboard
and confirm that the contract is active, the Cortex OS is online, and no alert
requires attention. A normal new member does not need samrepair.|000

|CK0Neonwake is available immediately. Run neonwake to wake every installed
implant into a carried lighting mesh if darkness prevents you from seeing a
room; run it again to switch the mesh off.|000

|CKB2. Review available firmware|000
|CK0Run samskills to see every routine, its Guild Level, resource use, and
current readiness. READY means the routine is available. A red HARDWARE status
means its required implant is missing. Use samhelp <routine> before deploying
unfamiliar firmware and samhelp firmware for the complete implant map.|000

|CKB3. Learn the combat loop|000
|CK0Snap Cut produces Edge whenever it deals damage, making it a dependable
way to establish momentum. Jolt offers lightning damage and becomes another
source of Edge while the Cortex is running hot. At GL2, Threat Scan reports a
foe's armour and resistances and establishes a lock that strengthens the next
Ripcut. A scanned Ripcut consumes that lock and produces Edge when it lands.|000

|CK0When Edge is available, most active routines automatically route one point
into a stronger version of their normal effect. The base routine still works at
zero Edge. Watch for the shell's EDGE ROUTE message to see when damage,
duration, shielding, healing, or control strength has been amplified.|000

|CK0Most successful active routines add Heat and all active routines use the
shared Cortex execution cycle. Redline can improve some offensive firmware,
but reaching the thermal ceiling locks Heat-producing routines until the
system cools. Overclock adds temporary headroom without producing Heat, at the
cost of wear to the Cortex OS. Watch the live state with monitor or samstatus.|000

|CKB4. Build the loadout|000
|CK0Rin Kade operates the restricted clinic beyond the contract office. Engage
Rin to inspect every current and future unlock. The catalog shows the implant
slot, grade, strain, and exact price before confirmation. Active members pay
for hardware but not guild-covered installation, extraction, or signature
repair services.|000

|CKB5. Maintain the hardware|000
|CK0Combat damage can wear down implant integrity, while firmware use can add
fragmentation. Dashboard names the affected process and shows whether to use
defrag, patch, purge, or reboot. Rin repairs physical integrity. Use logs when
you need to understand how a process reached its current state.|000

|CKB6. Use the network|000
|CK0Samwho lists connected Street Samurai, samchat transmits on the private
Cortex network, and samhist reviews recent transmissions. Samhelp network
explains the available syntax and visibility rules.|000

|CK0If a routine will not start, read its failure message first. Then check
samstatus for contract, Edge, Heat, and the Cortex cycle; check samskills for
Guild Level and hardware; and check dashboard for implant or maintenance
problems.|000
